    Malosini is essential, as is observing the mob's behavior when spells land vs. spells getting resisted.  Of course, if you have access to player cast root, snare, or blind you can minimize the potential danger of a pet root break. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujochangaladar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 533<br> <font color=#333333>(8/29/02 9:49:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=228.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: IR soloing ideas</span><hr size=1>    Well, finally got IR, and did a a little experimenting.<br>
<br>
    First off, I am only down to 7 second pets via Kobold Jester's Crown.  I need 3 more points for QS 1.  With the Crown that will drop it to 6 second pets.<br>
<br>
    Tried Shissar Stalkers.  I got in pretty close so I could see the spell messages, and waited for the pet root to take hold.  Once I did, I immediately reclaimed and resummoned.  70% of the time the root held long enough to get another pet up.  The other 30% the root dropped very early.  I would get beat on, typically interrupted, forcing me to zone.<br>
<br>
    Tried Timeless Golems.  Root held long enough to resummon probably 80% of the time.  If it didn't, I could easily run away and resummon before they caught up to me.<br>
<br>
    Rockfiends easily outrun any other mobs in the zone, so I haven't tried them yet.  Maybe once I get at least one level of Quick Summoning I can make an attempt.<br>
<br>
    1.  Malosini is essential<br>
    2.  Partnering with someone is very helpful at this stage.  2 mags works well, otherwise just about any class that can root or snare would make this tactic work.<br>
    3.  I need to get a Bioluminescent Orb.  Will make the gaps betwen pets safer.<br>
<br>
