s=title>   Re: IR soloing ideas</span><hr size=1>     I started attempting some bigger beasts lately, especially with the changes made in the last couple of patches.  I have successfully soloed a Goranga Scout...  soloed a Vampyre Bat...  soloed a Mind Burrower.  This basically means that I can take advantage of the improved xp for killing higher level mobs.  Against single targets, this skill puts me neck and neck with Druids and Necromancers, although I have much fewer tricks to deal with adds.  They still come out ahead somewhat because of this.<br>
<br>
   My earlier idea of trying to handle double golems in the Grey didn't pan out very well. On the first couple pets, the golems would assist each other on the pet, but by the third, one would focus on the pet and the other would gun for me, completely ignoring the pet.  I don't have any real explanation for it, but let it suffice to say that it's back to the drawing board when dealing with multiple mobs at once. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24>Levels 56-60</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
